# Banking Risk Intelligence — Demo HTTP Requests
# Works with: IntelliJ HTTP Client, VS Code REST Client extension
#
# Prerequisites:
#   App running with local profile:
#     ./mvnw spring-boot:run -Dspring-boot.run.profiles=local
#   docker compose up -d postgres redis
#
# Run steps in order. Copy token values from step 0 responses into @customer1_token etc.

@base = http://localhost:8080
@account1 = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011
@account2 = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012

# ─── Step 0: Acquire tokens (local profile only) ─────────────────────────────

### Get CUSTOMER1 token (USER_1 — no login anomaly, ACCOUNT_2 is known beneficiary)
GET {{base}}/dev/token?user=customer1

### Get CUSTOMER2 token (USER_2 — HAS login anomaly, no known beneficiaries)
GET {{base}}/dev/token?user=customer2

### Get ANALYST token
GET {{base}}/dev/token?user=analyst

# ── After running the three requests above, set these variables: ──────────────
@customer1_token = <paste token from customer1 response>
@customer2_token = <paste token from customer2 response>
@analyst_token   = <paste token from analyst response>

# ─── Step 1: LOW-risk transfer ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# USER_1 → $5.00 → ACCOUNT_2 (known beneficiary, no anomaly)
# Rules triggered: ACCOUNT_AGE_UNDER_7_DAYS (+20)
# Expected score: 20  |  Level: LOW  |  Status: POSTED  |  No AI call

### LOW transfer
POST {{base}}/api/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{customer1_token}}
Idempotency-Key: demo-low-001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountId": "{{account1}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{account2}}",
  "amountMinor": 500,
  "currency": "USD"
}

# ─── Step 2: MEDIUM-risk transfer ────────────────────────────────────────────
# USER_2 → $40.00 → ACCOUNT_1 (new beneficiary, login anomaly, age < 7 days)
# Rules triggered: NEW_BENEFICIARY (+25) + ACCOUNT_AGE_UNDER_7_DAYS (+20) + LOGIN_ANOMALY (+16)
# Expected score: 61  |  Level: MEDIUM  |  Status: POSTED  |  Async AI narrative queued

### MEDIUM transfer
POST {{base}}/api/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{customer2_token}}
Idempotency-Key: demo-medium-001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountId": "{{account2}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{account1}}",
  "amountMinor": 4000,
  "currency": "USD"
}

# ─── Step 3: HIGH-risk transfer #1 (will be APPROVED) ────────────────────────
# USER_2 → $5,100.00 → ACCOUNT_1
# Velocity from step 2 ($40.00) + current ($5,100.00) = $5,140.00 > $5,000.00 threshold
# Rules triggered: NEW_BENEFICIARY (+25) + ACCOUNT_AGE_UNDER_7_DAYS (+20)
#                  + LOGIN_ANOMALY (+16) + HOURLY_VELOCITY_OVER_5000 (+30)
# Expected score: 91  |  Level: HIGH  |  Status: PENDING_REVIEW
# Source funds HELD — destination NOT credited until analyst approves

### HIGH transfer #1 (save transferId → high1_transfer_id)
POST {{base}}/api/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{customer2_token}}
Idempotency-Key: demo-high-001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountId": "{{account2}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{account1}}",
  "amountMinor": 510000,
  "currency": "USD"
}

# ─── Step 4: HIGH-risk transfer #2 (will be REJECTED) ────────────────────────
# USER_2 → $1,000.00 → ACCOUNT_1
# Historical velocity: step2 ($40) + step3 ($5,100) = $5,140.00 already > $5,000.00 threshold
# Same rules as step 3 — velocity still above threshold

### HIGH transfer #2 (save transferId → high2_transfer_id)
POST {{base}}/api/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{customer2_token}}
Idempotency-Key: demo-high-002
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountId": "{{account2}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{account1}}",
  "amountMinor": 100000,
  "currency": "USD"
}

# ─── Step 5: List pending alerts (analyst dashboard) ─────────────────────────

### List REVIEW_PENDING alerts
GET {{base}}/api/analyst/alerts?status=REVIEW_PENDING
Authorization: Bearer {{analyst_token}}

# ── Copy alertId values for the two HIGH transfers into these variables: ───────
@high1_alert_id = <paste alertId for high transfer #1>
@high2_alert_id = <paste alertId for high transfer #2>

# ─── Step 6: Analyst APPROVE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Approving HIGH #1: held funds settle to destination (ACCOUNT_1 credited)
# Transfer moves from PENDING_REVIEW → POSTED
# Source held balance released to destination

### Approve HIGH alert #1
POST {{base}}/api/analyst/alerts/{{high1_alert_id}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{analyst_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Verified with customer via phone — legitimate business transfer"
}

# ─── Step 7: Analyst REJECT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Rejecting HIGH #2: held funds return to source (ACCOUNT_2 balance restored)
# Transfer moves from PENDING_REVIEW → REJECTED

### Reject HIGH alert #2
POST {{base}}/api/analyst/alerts/{{high2_alert_id}}/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{analyst_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Unable to verify customer — transfer pattern consistent with account takeover"
}

# ─── Step 8: Idempotency retry ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Resend step 1 with the exact same Idempotency-Key.
# Expected: same transferId returned, no new ledger entries.

### Idempotency retry (same key as step 1)
POST {{base}}/api/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{customer1_token}}
Idempotency-Key: demo-low-001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountId": "{{account1}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{account2}}",
  "amountMinor": 500,
  "currency": "USD"
}

# ─── Step 9: Actuator health check ───────────────────────────────────────────

### Health (no auth required)
GET {{base}}/actuator/health

# ─── Step 10: Metrics ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Transfer creation latency histogram
GET {{base}}/actuator/metrics/transfer.creation.latency
Authorization: Bearer {{analyst_token}}

### Risk level distribution
GET {{base}}/actuator/metrics/risk.level.count
Authorization: Bearer {{analyst_token}}

### Idempotency cache hit counter
GET {{base}}/actuator/metrics/idempotency.cache.hit
Authorization: Bearer {{analyst_token}}

### Prometheus scrape endpoint (for Grafana)
GET {{base}}/actuator/prometheus
Authorization: Bearer {{analyst_token}}
